<ns4510:section xmlns:ns4510="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4511:title xmlns:ns4511="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Six Sigma for reducing process variation</ns4511:title>
    <ns4512:para xmlns:ns4512="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        If reliability is your game then continuous process improvement is usually a necessity. For this
        organizations commonly use six sigma, a quality management approach developed by Motorola.
        Six sigma is meant to continuously optimize processes in order to eliminate process defects
        (see for example <ns4513:xref xmlns:ns4513="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="Pande-Neumann-Cavanaugh-2000"/>).
        It has the following six core components
      <ns4514:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4514="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4515:listitem xmlns:ns4515="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4516:formalpara xmlns:ns4516="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4517:title xmlns:ns4517="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Visualize</ns4517:title>
          <ns4518:para xmlns:ns4518="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            where one improves ones understanding of customer, business and benchmark goals and performs
            an initial gap analysis to understand how far one is from achieving these,
          </ns4518:para>
        </ns4516:formalpara></ns4515:listitem>
        <ns4519:listitem xmlns:ns4519="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4520:formalpara xmlns:ns4520="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4521:title xmlns:ns4521="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Commit</ns4521:title>
          <ns4522:para xmlns:ns4522="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            where the various parties commit to making the changes required to achieve these goals. This may
            include team building negotiation and contract renegotiation.
          </ns4522:para>
        </ns4520:formalpara></ns4519:listitem>
        <ns4523:listitem xmlns:ns4523="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4524:formalpara xmlns:ns4524="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4525:title xmlns:ns4525="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Prioritization</ns4525:title>
          <ns4526:para xmlns:ns4526="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            which includes refining the gap analysis, task prioritization, project planning,
          </ns4526:para>
        </ns4524:formalpara></ns4523:listitem>
        <ns4527:listitem xmlns:ns4527="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4528:formalpara xmlns:ns4528="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4529:title xmlns:ns4529="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Characterization</ns4529:title>
          <ns4530:para xmlns:ns4530="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            which includes root cause, value stream, capacity and risk analysis, process flow characterization and metrics,
          </ns4530:para>
        </ns4528:formalpara></ns4527:listitem>
        <ns4531:listitem xmlns:ns4531="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4532:formalpara xmlns:ns4532="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4533:title xmlns:ns4533="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Improvement</ns4533:title>
          <ns4534:para xmlns:ns4534="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            which covers improvement of organizational architecture, business process workflows, and
            quality processes and metrics, deployment of these processes and training,
          </ns4534:para>
        </ns4532:formalpara></ns4531:listitem>
        <ns4535:listitem xmlns:ns4535="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4536:formalpara xmlns:ns4536="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4537:title xmlns:ns4537="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Achieve</ns4537:title>
          <ns4538:para xmlns:ns4538="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            which includes improvement of the deployment metrics, communication including sharing of the lessons learnt
            and updated best practices across the organization.
          </ns4538:para>
        </ns4536:formalpara></ns4535:listitem>
      </ns4514:itemizedlist>
      
      
    </ns4512:para>
  </ns4510:section>